1.10
log
@move a few links from http:// to https://
@
text
@<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN">
<html>
<head>
<title>OpenSMTPD: Manual Pages</title>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=iso-8859-1">
<meta name="description" content="OpenSMTPD Manual Pages">
<meta name="copyright" content="This document copyright 2016 by OpenBSD.">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="openbsd.css">
<link rel="canonical" href="https://www.opensmtpd.org/manual.html">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#23238E">

<h2>
<a href="index.html">
<font color="#0000ff"><i>Open</i></font><font color="#000084">SMTPD</font></a>
<font color="#e00000">Manual Pages</font>
</h2>
<hr>

Web manual pages are available from
<a href="https://www.openbsd.org/">OpenBSD</a>.
These manual pages reflect the latest development release of OpenSMTPD.<p>

<ul>
 <li><a href="https://man.openbsd.org/smtpd">smtpd</a>
     - Simple Mail Transfer Protocol daemon

 <li><a href="https://man.openbsd.org/smtpd.conf">smtpd.conf</a>
     - Simple Mail Transfer Protocol daemon configuration file

 <li><a href="https://man.openbsd.org/smtpctl">smtpctl</a>
     - control the Simple Mail Transfer Protocol daemon

 <li><a href="https://man.openbsd.org/newaliases">newaliases</a>
     - generate alias mappings for the Simple Mail Transfer Protocol daemon

 <li><a href="https://man.openbsd.org/makemap">makemap</a>
     - generate mappings for the Simple Mail Transfer Protocol daemon

 <li><a href="https://man.openbsd.org/aliases">aliases</a>
     - aliases files format

 <li><a href="https://man.openbsd.org/forward">forward</a>
     - forwarding files format

 <li><a href="https://man.openbsd.org/table">table</a>
     - format description for smtpd tables

 <li><a href="https://man.openbsd.org/sendmail">sendmail</a>
     - a mail enqueuer for smtpd
</ul>

The SMTP protocol implemented in OpenSMTPD is described in
<a href="https://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc5321.txt">RFC 5321</a>.

</body>
</html>
@


